ess/OS contract checks, so System is not mandatory. Rejection-gate: Agentic is disqualified because persistence correctness does not depend on judging LLM output quality.","test_description":"Execute chat flow against a real local test DB (transactional), including a regeneration path; read back stored rows and assert all exchange parts exist with correct linkage/order and expected timestamp fields.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"This validates real module wiring and DB persistence beyond unit scope without requiring full external system checks.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.07,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.16,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the tone check triggers regeneration, the second response replaces the first — the customer never sees the rejected draft.","required_reality_check_level":"System","justification":"SYSTEM TRIAD (3): behavior explicitly requires proving an externally visible side effect ('customer never sees' rejected draft). Unit/integration can verify internal state but can miss leakage at delivery boundary. This needs round-trip observation at the external interface (e.g., API/UI response stream). Rejection-gate: Integration is disqualified by explicit external-visibility requirement in behavior text.","test_description":"Trigger a tone-regeneration scenario through the real delivery boundary (HTTP/chat endpoint or UI transport), then assert the customer-visible response contains only regenerated content and never exposes the first draft (including stream/chunk paths if applicable).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"The test requires external round-trip verification of what is actually shown, which matches System.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.58,"Agentic":0.2,"Workflow":0.12}}]}
